Subject: Re: [T2] Oil Leak and Valve Cover Gaskets

Jason Meyer wrote:
> Come to find out after taking a look at the way the oil was leaking onto my
> heater boxes that it was again coming from my valves. Last time I had this
> problem, I found that the heat had warped the gaskets and caused them to
> bend inward allowing for leaks to occur.
>   
Others use grease, I use weatherstrip cement or permatex (the one that 
holds gaskets).  That way it ensures that the gasket doesn't move upon 
installation.  Also, put a thin coat of oil (just like you do with oil 
filter) on the gasket before installation.  This will help it seal with 
the head.

Mike
